{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1905,"text":"So, without romanticizing this too much:"},{"time":4388,"text":"imagine that you light your home\nwith kerosene and candles every night,"},{"time":8048,"text":"and that you do all of your cooking"},{"time":9765,"text":"with charcoal."},{"time":10950,"text":"This is how the world's\ntwo billion poorest people"},{"time":13836,"text":"cook and light their homes every day."},{"time":15921,"text":"This isn't just inconvenient,"},{"time":17929,"text":"this is inefficient,"},{"time":19607,"text":"it's expensive,"},{"time":20891,"text":"it's harmful to human health,\nharmful to the environment,"},{"time":23605,"text":"and it's unproductive."},{"time":24806,"text":"And that's energy poverty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26159,"text":"So let me give you a couple of examples."},{"time":28089,"text":"I work in Haiti,"},{"time":29430,"text":"where about 80% of the population\nlives in energy poverty."},{"time":33737,"text":"The average household\nspends 10% of its income"},{"time":37567,"text":"on kerosene for lighting –"},{"time":39429,"text":"that's an order of magnitude greater\nthan what the average US household spends"},{"time":44646,"text":"on electricity to light their homes."},{"time":47232,"text":"The 2008 hurricane season in Haiti caused"},{"time":49480,"text":"about one billion dollars in damage."},{"time":51699,"text":"That was a sixth of their GDP."},{"time":54081,"text":"The damage was so severe"},{"time":55417,"text":"because the primary energy fuel\nin Haiti is charcoal,"},{"time":58950,"text":"which is made from trees,"},{"time":60342,"text":"and has left the country\nalmost completely deforested."},{"time":63116,"text":"Without trees, the country can't absorb\nheavy rains and massive flooding,"},{"time":67873,"text":"as a result."},{"time":69234,"text":"So in the industrialized world,"},{"time":70824,"text":"we built walls that protect us\nfrom the externalities of our energy use;"},{"time":74753,"text":"we can afford to clean up acute\nenvironmental disasters;"},{"time":78490,"text":"and we can also afford\nto adapt to chronic conditions"},{"time":81806,"text":"like climate change."},{"time":83430,"text":"That's not the case for Haiti.\nThey can't afford this."},{"time":86119,"text":"The only way they're going to lift\nthemselves out of energy poverty"},{"time":89319,"text":"is by adapting fuels\nthat are more efficient,"},{"time":92028,"text":"that are less expensive,"},{"time":93552,"text":"that are better for human health,\nbetter for the environment"},{"time":96562,"text":"and that are more productive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98045,"text":"So it turns out that those fuels\nand technologies exist,"},{"time":100755,"text":"and this is an example of that."},{"time":102358,"text":"This is a solar LED lightbulb"},{"time":105185,"text":"that we sell for a retail price\nof about 10 dollars in rural Haiti."},{"time":110656,"text":"That's a payback period\nof less than three months"},{"time":113147,"text":"for the average Haitian household."},{"time":117839,"text":"The prescriptions to solve energy poverty\nseems pretty straightforward:"},{"time":121329,"text":"you develop these technologies\nthat have a great return on investment,"},{"time":124738,"text":"and people should be snatching them up."},{"time":126675,"text":"But that's not the case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128056,"text":"The first time I ever went down to Haiti\nwas in August of 2008,"},{"time":131278,"text":"sort of on a whim,"},{"time":132515,"text":"and I was fielding surveys\nin the rural south of the country"},{"time":135421,"text":"to assess the extent of energy poverty."},{"time":137848,"text":"And at night, I would go around sometimes"},{"time":140210,"text":"and I would speak with the street vendors"},{"time":142421,"text":"and see if they were interested\nin buying these solar LED lamps."},{"time":145707,"text":"One woman who I encountered\nturned down my offer,"},{"time":148575,"text":"and she said, “Mon chéri,\nc'est trop Cher,”"},{"time":151090,"text":"which basically means,\n“My dear, it's too expensive.”"},{"time":153802,"text":"But I tried to explain to her,"},{"time":155291,"text":"“Look, this is going to save you\na lot of money,"},{"time":157585,"text":"and it's going to give\nyou even better light"},{"time":159680,"text":"than what you're using\nnow with the kerosene.”"},{"time":162044,"text":"So I didn't make the sale,"},{"time":163410,"text":"but I did learn a really important lesson,"},{"time":165901,"text":"which is that technology, products,"},{"time":167933,"text":"were not going to end energy poverty."},{"time":170514,"text":"Instead, access was going to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172722,"text":"Specifically, there are\ntwo types of access"},{"time":175263,"text":"that are going to end energy poverty:"},{"time":177291,"text":"there's physical access,\nand there's financial access."},{"time":180907,"text":"So, physical access --"},{"time":182829,"text":"what does that mean?"},{"time":184406,"text":"It's very expensive for low-income\nhouseholds in developing countries"},{"time":188665,"text":"to reach major centers of commerce."},{"time":190495,"text":"And it's basically impossible for them\nto order something off Amazon.com."},{"time":194447,"text":"“The last mile” is a phrase\nthat's normally associated"},{"time":197237,"text":"with the telecommunications industry."},{"time":199086,"text":"It means that last bit\nof wire that's necessary"},{"time":201350,"text":"to connect the customer to the provider."},{"time":203568,"text":"What we need for ending energy poverty\nare last-mile retailers"},{"time":209223,"text":"that bring these clean energy\nproducts to the people."},{"time":212255,"text":"The kerosene and charcoal value chains\nalready figured this out:"},{"time":215415,"text":"those fuels are ubiquitous\nacross the entire country."},{"time":218909,"text":"You can go to the most remote\nvillage in Haiti"},{"time":221378,"text":"and you will find somebody\nselling kerosene and charcoal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224787,"text":"So the other type of access: financial."},{"time":227250,"text":"We all know that clean energy\nproducts, technologies,"},{"time":231136,"text":"tend to be characterized\nby higher upfront costs,"},{"time":233719,"text":"but very low operating costs."},{"time":235351,"text":"And so in the industrialized world,"},{"time":237175,"text":"we have very generous subsidies\nthat are specifically designed"},{"time":240221,"text":"to bring down those upfront costs."},{"time":242813,"text":"Those subsidies don't exist in Haiti."},{"time":244912,"text":"What they do have is microfinance."},{"time":247420,"text":"But you're going to severely diminish\nthe value proposition"},{"time":250268,"text":"of your clean energy product"},{"time":251702,"text":"if you expect somebody in Haiti\nto go out, get a microloan,"},{"time":255151,"text":"go back to the retailer,"},{"time":256580,"text":"and then buy the clean energy product."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259500,"text":"So the prescription to end energy poverty\nis much more complicated"},{"time":263412,"text":"than simply products."},{"time":265446,"text":"We need to integrate financial access"},{"time":268193,"text":"directly into new, innovative\ndistribution models."},{"time":272323,"text":"What does that mean?"},{"time":273512,"text":"That means bundling consumer credit\nwith the retailer."},{"time":276744,"text":"This is really easy\nfor Bloomingdale’s to do,"},{"time":279518,"text":"but it's not so easy for a rural\nsales agent in Haiti to do."},{"time":283508,"text":"We need to redirect cash flows"},{"time":286211,"text":"that are going now\nfrom the diaspora in the United States"},{"time":289219,"text":"through Western Union\nwire transfers in cash"},{"time":292509,"text":"directly into clean energy products"},{"time":294387,"text":"that can be delivered to or picked up by\ntheir friends or family in Haiti."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298247,"text":"So the next time you hear\nabout a technology or product"},{"time":301357,"text":"that's going to change the world,"},{"time":303041,"text":"be a little bit skeptical."},{"time":304462,"text":"The inventor Dean Kamen,\nthe guy who invented the Segway,"},{"time":308141,"text":"a genius by any standards,"},{"time":309922,"text":"once said that his job is easy,\ninventing things is easy,"},{"time":315199,"text":"the hard part is the technology\ndissemination --"},{"time":318294,"text":"it's getting those\ntechnologies and products"},{"time":320445,"text":"to the people who need it most."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322032,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323231,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}